    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I think the reason is simply to work around browser security policies. Chrome for example refuses to execute HTTP AJAX calls if the page itself was loaded over HTTPS. Still though I don't think interfacing a webpage directly with a locally running node is a good thing, neither can I imagine users allowing it, so I don't think this is really something we should be investing time in.\n",
